Phase 1 — Database agent summary.

The Phase 0 migration set, RLS policies, GiST geo-indexes, seed data, and
shared types were authored at the close of Phase 0 (see
orchestration-logs/phase-0/Database_Agent.log) and have not drifted in
Phase 1. Three downstream agents have already shipped against the frozen
contract on this branch — Auth & Identity, Core API (profiles), and the
QA test harness (which authored an RLS suite that targets these exact
policies) — none of which required any schema change.

## WHAT I DID

- **Re-reviewed the migration set** in `supabase/migrations/` and
  confirmed every file is idempotent and unchanged since Phase 0:
  `20260515000100_init.sql` (extensions + 10 enums + `set_updated_at`),
  `…000200_users.sql`, `…000300_requests_and_bookings.sql`,
  `…000400_payments_messages_reviews.sql`, `…000500_indexes.sql`,
  `…000600_rls.sql`. All `create … if not exists` / `do $$ … $$` enum
  guards / `drop policy if exists` in place; the same files will apply
  cleanly across dev, staging, and (eventually) production.
- **Geo-indexes verified statically.** Three PostGIS GiST indexes are
  declared on the geography columns:
  - `companion_profiles_service_area_gix` on
    `companion_profiles.service_area_center`
  - `bookings_restaurant_location_gix` on `bookings.restaurant_location`
  - `meal_requests_proposed_location_gix` on
    `meal_requests.proposed_location`
  `scripts/db/verify.sql` already asserts (a) all three exist and (b)
  the companion service-area index is actually GiST (not btree).
- **Confirmed the frozen schema contract is intact.** No edits to
  `supabase/migrations/*`, `supabase/seed/seed.sql`,
  `lib/types/enums.ts`, or `lib/types/database.ts` in Phase 1.
  Phase 0's "Frozen contract (Phase 1)" section in
  `supabase/README.md` is still accurate. Downstream agents (Auth,
  Core API, QA) have consumed it without requesting changes.
- **Validated RLS policy authorship against the published model.** The
  policies in `…000600_rls.sql` match the published quick-reference in
  `supabase/README.md` and the QA agent's RLS suite
  (`tests/rls/policies.test.ts`) targets them clause-for-clause. Once
  run against a live database, the suite is the executable proof; it
  self-skips today because `TEST_SUPABASE_*` env vars are not set.

## WHAT I COULD NOT DO

- **Run `npm run db:migrate` against dev or staging.** Both prerequisites
  documented in `supabase/README.md` are absent locally:
  1. `psql` is not installed on this machine (`which psql` → not found).
  2. `DATABASE_URL` is not exported and the project's `.env.local` ships
     only the Supabase project URL plus anon/service-role keys — no
     Postgres password and no connection string. The backup
     `.env.local~` carries an empty `SUPABASE_DB_PASSWORD=`.
  These belong to Foundations / the founder, so the actual `db:migrate`
  invocation is recorded as a manual checkpoint.
- **Run `scripts/db/verify.sql`.** Same blocker: needs `psql` +
  `DATABASE_URL`.
- **Run `npm run db:seed` against dev.** Same blocker.
- **Run the QA agent's RLS suite (`npm run test:rls`) end-to-end.** The
  suite is authored and ready, but `tests/_helpers/env.ts` requires
  `TEST_SUPABASE_URL`, `TEST_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`, and
  `TEST_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY` to be set and pointed at a *disposable*
  Supabase project (deliberately not the dev project, so a misconfigured
  shell can't corrupt the team's dev data). The suite `describe.skipIf`s
  out without them — so it runs green but covers nothing today.

## INTERFACES PUBLISHED

The Phase 0 frozen contract is unchanged in Phase 1. Authoritative
artifacts re-asserted here for clarity:

- **Migration set** — `supabase/migrations/20260515000100..600_*.sql`.
  Eight tables (`users`, `companion_profiles`, `availability`,
  `meal_requests`, `bookings`, `payments`, `messages`, `reviews`),
  ten enums, three PostGIS GiST geo-indexes, RLS enabled on every
  public table, and the `public.is_booking_participant(uuid)` helper.
- **Shared types & enums** — `lib/types/index.ts` re-exports
  `enums.ts` (string-literal unions + `REQUEST_NEXT_STATES` /
  `BOOKING_NEXT_STATES`) and `database.ts` (`Database` generic with
  `Row`/`Insert`/`Update` shapes for every table). Already consumed by
  `lib/supabase/{client,server}.ts`, the Auth & Identity flow, and the
  `/api/profiles` module.
- **Seed identities** — four `joinmytable.test` accounts
  (`ava.seeker@`, `ben.companion@`, `cleo.both@`, `dan.unverified@`),
  password `Password123!`, ready to load via `npm run db:seed` once
  the manual checkpoint clears.
- **Runner contract** — `npm run db:migrate` / `npm run db:seed`
  (`scripts/db/{migrate,seed}.sh`): idempotent, `DATABASE_URL`-driven,
  `APP_ENV=production` blocks seed.
- **Verifier** — `scripts/db/verify.sql` is the post-migrate smoke
  gate (extensions, enums, tables, RLS-on, GiST indexes, helper fn,
  policy names).

No new published interfaces this phase; nothing changed, nothing
deprecated.

## MANUAL CHECKPOINTS

The actual cloud-side rollout below is operator work — it modifies
Supabase project state and needs credentials this sandbox does not
have. None of it is blocked on more Database-agent code.

1. **Install `psql`.** macOS: `brew install libpq && brew link --force libpq`
   (or `brew install postgresql@16`). CI: install the postgres client
   in the job image.
2. **Get the Supabase Postgres connection strings.**
   Project Settings → Database → Connection string. Pattern:
   `postgresql://postgres:<DB_PASSWORD>@db.<PROJECT_REF>.supabase.co:5432/postgres`.
   Keep dev and staging credentials separate; never commit either.
3. **Apply migrations to dev:**
   ```
   DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:<dev-pass>@db.<dev-ref>.supabase.co:5432/postgres" \
     npm run db:migrate
   psql "$DATABASE_URL" -v ON_ERROR_STOP=1 -f scripts/db/verify.sql
   ```
   The verifier must end with `verify: ok - extensions, enums, tables, RLS, GiST indexes, helpers, and policies are all present.`
4. **Apply migrations to staging:** same incantation against the
   staging `DATABASE_URL`. Re-runs are no-ops by design.
5. **Seed dev:**
   ```
   APP_ENV=development \
   DATABASE_URL="postgresql://postgres:<dev-pass>@db.<dev-ref>.supabase.co:5432/postgres" \
     npm run db:seed
   ```
   The seed script refuses to run against `APP_ENV=production`.
   Staging seed is optional; production must never receive seed data.
6. **Exercise RLS against the live policies.** Provision a *disposable*
   Supabase project (not dev, not staging) and export
   `TEST_SUPABASE_URL` / `TEST_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY` /
   `TEST_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY`, then run
   `npm run test:rls`. The suite at `tests/rls/policies.test.ts`
   covers every users / companion_profiles / availability policy
   clause-for-clause; meal_requests / bookings / payments / messages /
   reviews participant-vs-non-participant coverage will land when the
   Core API agent finishes those modules in a later phase
   (already noted in that file).
7. **Open product decisions still routed to the founder via the
   Orchestrator** (carried over from Phase 0 — none of these gate
   migration application, but each will spawn a follow-up migration):
   - Platform fee % (`payments.platform_fee_cents` exists; rule TBD).
   - Escrow release trigger (column wiring exists; semantics TBD —
     Payments + Core API).
   - Cancellation policy (`bookings.cancelled_by`,
     `payments.escrow_status='refunded'` wired; refund tier rules TBD).
   - Trust & Safety review of `reviews_select_public` (currently
     world-readable so companion profiles can render ratings; T&S
     may want to gate reviews-of-seekers to verified booking partners
     only).
